3. If prod workspace is deleted, what happens?
Workspace deletion removes state reference locally
Actual resources in AWS will NOT be deleted
But Terraform loses tracking of those resources

4. Can we recover state from S3 backend after workspace deletion?
Yes ✅
Since state is in S3 backend, it still exists
Create new workspace → reconfigure backend → Terraform will pull state
May need to run:
terraform init
terraform workspace new prod
If mismatch → use terraform state commands

6. what happens if a provider is getting upgraded? for example, you are in an AWS 7.5 provider, and that needs to be updated to 7.6. It's a major version. So how do you plan for this?
First check release notes / breaking changes
Update version in required_providers
Run terraform init -upgrade
Test in dev environment first
Validate with terraform plan
Then promote to QA → PROD
Always avoid direct upgrade in production

